## OTel Span Attribute Naming Convention

This codebase follows a **two-tier** naming strategy, explicitly documented in the comments of `span-factory.ts`:

### 1. **OTel GenAI Semantic Convention attributes** (canonical, no prefix)
Use the official OTel GenAI semconv names whenever one exists. These use `snake_case` and the `gen_ai.` prefix:

| Attribute | Example |
|---|---|
| `gen_ai.system` | `"vllm"` |
| `gen_ai.request.model` | model name |
| `gen_ai.operation.name` | `"execute_tool"` |
| `gen_ai.tool.name` | tool name |
| `gen_ai.usage.input_tokens` | number |
| `gen_ai.usage.output_tokens` | number |
| `gen_ai.response.finish_reasons` | string array |

### 2. **Emmy-specific extensions** (custom prefix)
When semconv has no coverage, use the `emmy.` prefix with `snake_case` sub-keys:

| Attribute | Example |
|---|---|
| `emmy.prompt.sha256` | prompt hash |
| `emmy.profile.id` | profile identifier |
| `emmy.profile.version` | profile version |
| `emmy.profile.hash` | profile content hash |
| `emmy.profile.variant` | variant name |
| `emmy.profile.variant_hash` | variant hash |
| `emmy.role` | turn role |
| `emmy.tool.args_hash` | tool arguments hash |

### Key rule (from the code comments):
> "Rather than stamp the attributes ad-hoc at every call site (D-10 anti-pattern — inventing emmy-specific names where OTel semconv already has canonical ones), we funnel span creation through the helpers below and only add emmy-specific attrs where semconv has no coverage."

In short: **use `gen_ai.*` from OTel semconv first; fall back to `emmy.*` with `snake_case` only when no canonical attribute exists.**
